swL2MgmtMIB.name: swL2MgmtMIB
swL2MgmtMIB.description: The Structure of Layer 2 Network Management Information.

IANAifMauAutoNegCapBits.name: IANAifMauAutoNegCapBits
IANAifMauAutoNegCapBits.description: This data type is used as the syntax of the swL2PortAutoNegCapabilityBits, swL2PortAutoNegCapAdvertisedBits, and swL2PortAutoNegCapReceivedBits objects in swL2PortAutoNegTable.

swDevInfoTotalNumOfPort.name: swDevInfoTotalNumOfPort
swDevInfoTotalNumOfPort.description: The number of ports within this switch. This value is the sum of the ports within this switch.

swDevInfoNumOfPortInUse.name: swDevInfoNumOfPortInUse
swDevInfoNumOfPortInUse.description: The number of ports in this switch connected to the segment or the end stations.

swDevModuleInfoTable.name: swDevModuleInfoTable
swDevModuleInfoTable.description: This table contains the module information.

swDevModuleInfoEntry.name: swDevModuleInfoEntry
swDevModuleInfoEntry.description: A list of management information for each unit in the system.

swDevModuleInfoUnitID.name: swDevModuleInfoUnitID
swDevModuleInfoUnitID.description: This object indicates the specific unit ID in the stacking/chassis table.

swDevModuleInfoModuleName.name: swDevModuleInfoModuleName
swDevModuleInfoModuleName.description: A text string containing the name of the module.

swDevModuleInfoReversion.name: swDevModuleInfoReversion
swDevModuleInfoReversion.description: A text string containing the version (name or number) of the module.

swDevModuleInfoSerial.name: swDevModuleInfoSerial
swDevModuleInfoSerial.description: A text string containing the serial number or serial name of the module.

swDevModuleInfoDescription.name: swDevModuleInfoDescription
swDevModuleInfoDescription.description: A text string containing a description of the module.

swL2DevCtrlStpState.name: swL2DevCtrlStpState
swL2DevCtrlStpState.description: This object can enable or disable the spanning tree algorithm during the runtime of the system.

swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping.name: swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping
swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping.description: This object indicates if the layer 2 Internet Group Management Protocol (IGMP) capture function is enabled or disabled.

swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnoopingMcstRTOnly.name: swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnoopingMcstRTOnly
swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnoopingMcstRTOnly.description: This object controls the IGMP snooping forward multicast routing only state.

swL2DevCtrlRmonState.name: swL2DevCtrlRmonState
swL2DevCtrlRmonState.description: This object can enable or disable RMON.

swL2DevCtrlSnmpTrapState.name: swL2DevCtrlSnmpTrapState
swL2DevCtrlSnmpTrapState.description: This object controls the SNMP trap status.

swL2DevCtrlCleanAllStatisticCounter.name: swL2DevCtrlCleanAllStatisticCounter
swL2DevCtrlCleanAllStatisticCounter.description: When the object is set to active, all statistical counters will be cleared. If set to normal, no action will occur.

swL2DevCtrlVlanIdOfFDBTbl.name: swL2DevCtrlVlanIdOfFDBTbl
swL2DevCtrlVlanIdOfFDBTbl.description: Indicates the VLAN ID to which the Dot1dTpFdbTable belongs; The default value is the DEFAULT_VLAN_ID of the system.

swL2MACNotifyState.name: swL2MACNotifyState
swL2MACNotifyState.description: This object can enable or disable MAC Notification.

swL2MACNotifyHistorySize.name: swL2MACNotifyHistorySize
swL2MACNotifyHistorySize.description: This object indicates the history size of MAC addresses in the MAC Address table. The default value is 1.

swL2MACNotifyInterval.name: swL2MACNotifyInterval
swL2MACNotifyInterval.description: This object indicates the time interval, in seconds, that will trigger MAC notification messages.

swL2DevCtrlAsymVlanState.name: swL2DevCtrlAsymVlanState
swL2DevCtrlAsymVlanState.description: This object enables or disables asymmetric VLANs during the runtime of the system.

swL2DevCtrlTelnetState.name: swL2DevCtrlTelnetState
swL2DevCtrlTelnetState.description: This object controls the Telnet status.

swL2DevCtrlTelnetTcpPort.name: swL2DevCtrlTelnetTcpPort
swL2DevCtrlTelnetTcpPort.description: This object designates TCP ports. When Telnet is disabled, this object is not accessible.

swL2DevCtrlManagementVlanId.name: swL2DevCtrlManagementVlanId
swL2DevCtrlManagementVlanId.description: This object controls which previously created VLANs are included in the System IP Interface.

swL2DevCtrlWebState.name: swL2DevCtrlWebState
swL2DevCtrlWebState.description: This object controls the Web status.

swL2DevCtrlWebTcpPort.name: swL2DevCtrlWebTcpPort
swL2DevCtrlWebTcpPort.description: This object designates TCP ports. When Web is disabled, this object is not accessible.

swL2DevCtrlLLDPState.name: swL2DevCtrlLLDPState
swL2DevCtrlLLDPState.description: Specifies the state of the LLDP function. When this function is enabled, the switch can start to transmit LLDP packets and receive and process the LLDP packets. The specific function of each port will depend on the per port LLDP setting. For the advertisement of LLDP packets, the switch announces the information to its neighbor through ports. For receiving LLDP packets, the switch will learn the information from the LLDP packets advertised from the neighbor in the neighbor table.

swL2DevCtrlLLDPForwardMessageState.name: swL2DevCtrlLLDPForwardMessageState
swL2DevCtrlLLDPForwardMessageState.description: When lldp is disabled and lldp forward_message's are enabled, the LLDP Data Unit packets received by the switch will be forwarded.

swL2DevCtrlIpAutoconfig.name: swL2DevCtrlIpAutoconfig
swL2DevCtrlIpAutoconfig.description: This object controls the IP auto configuration state.

swL2DevCtrlCFMState.name: swL2DevCtrlCFMState
swL2DevCtrlCFMState.description: This object indicates the CFM global state.

swL2DevCtrlCFMPortTable.name: swL2DevCtrlCFMPortTable
swL2DevCtrlCFMPortTable.description: A table containing the CFM state of specified ports.

swL2DevCtrlCFMPortEntry.name: swL2DevCtrlCFMPortEntry
swL2DevCtrlCFMPortEntry.description: The entry of the CFM state on specified ports.

swL2DevCtrlCFMPortIndex.name: swL2DevCtrlCFMPortIndex
swL2DevCtrlCFMPortIndex.description: This object indicates the port number.

swL2DevCtrlCFMPortState.name: swL2DevCtrlCFMPortState
swL2DevCtrlCFMPortState.description: This object indicates the CFM state by port.

swL2DevCtrlCFMMaTable.name: swL2DevCtrlCFMMaTable
swL2DevCtrlCFMMaTable.description: A table containing the CFM mode of specified MAs.

swL2DevCtrlCFMMaEntry.name: swL2DevCtrlCFMMaEntry
swL2DevCtrlCFMMaEntry.description: The entry of the CFM mode on specified MAs.

swL2DevCtrlCFMMaMode.name: swL2DevCtrlCFMMaMode
swL2DevCtrlCFMMaMode.description: This object indicates the CFM mode by MA.

swL2DevCtrlCFMMepTable.name: swL2DevCtrlCFMMepTable
swL2DevCtrlCFMMepTable.description: A table containing the CFM mode of specified MEPs.

swL2DevCtrlCFMMepEntry.name: swL2DevCtrlCFMMepEntry
swL2DevCtrlCFMMepEntry.description: The entry of the CFM mode on specified MEPs.

swL2DevCtrlCFMMepMode.name: swL2DevCtrlCFMMepMode
swL2DevCtrlCFMMepMode.description: This object indicates the CFM mode by MEP.

swL2DevCtrlVLANTrunkState.name: swL2DevCtrlVLANTrunkState
swL2DevCtrlVLANTrunkState.description: This indicates the global state of the VLAN trunking feature of the device.

swL2DevCtrlIpAutoconfigTimeout.name: swL2DevCtrlIpAutoconfigTimeout
swL2DevCtrlIpAutoconfigTimeout.description: This object indicates the timeout for the auto configuration.

swL2DevAlarmNewRoot.name: swL2DevAlarmNewRoot
swL2DevAlarmNewRoot.description: When the device has become the new root of the Spanning Tree, this object decides whether to send a new root trap.

swL2DevAlarmTopologyChange.name: swL2DevAlarmTopologyChange
swL2DevAlarmTopologyChange.description: This object determines whether or not to send a trap message when the switch topology changes. If the object is enabled (3), the Topology Change trap is sent by the device when any of its configured ports transition from the Learning state to the Forwarding state, or from the Forwarding state to the Blocking state. For the same port transition, the device does not send the trap if this object value is disabled or in another state.

swL2DevAlarmLinkChange.name: swL2DevAlarmLinkChange
swL2DevAlarmLinkChange.description: This object determines whether or not to send a trap message when the link changes. If the object is enabled (3), the Link Change trap is sent by the device when any of its port links change. The device does not send the trap if this object value is disabled or in another state.

swL2VlanStaticTable.name: swL2VlanStaticTable
swL2VlanStaticTable.description: A table containing static configuration information for each VLAN configured into the device by (local or network) management. All entries are permanent and will be restored after the device is reset.

swL2VlanStaticEntry.name: swL2VlanStaticEntry
swL2VlanStaticEntry.description: Static information for a VLAN configured into this device by (local or network) management.

swL2VlanIndex.name: swL2VlanIndex
swL2VlanIndex.description: The VLAN-ID or other identifier referring to this VLAN.

swL2VLANAdvertisement.name: swL2VLANAdvertisement
swL2VLANAdvertisement.description: This object indicates if the advertisement is active or not.

swL2PVIDAutoAssignmentState.name: swL2PVIDAutoAssignmentState
swL2PVIDAutoAssignmentState.description: This object controls the PVID auto assignment state. If 'Auto-assign PVID' is disabled, the PVID can only be changed by PVID configuration (user changes explicitly). The VLAN configuration will not automatically change the PVID. If 'Auto-assign PVID' is enabled, the PVID will be changed by PVID or VLAN configuration. When a user configures a port to VLAN X's untagged membership, this port's PVID will be updated with VLAN X. Using the VLAN list command, PVID is updated as the last item of the VLAN list. When a user removes a port from the untagged membership of the PVID's VLAN, the port's PVID will be assigned 'default VLAN'.

swL2VlanPortInfoTable.name: swL2VlanPortInfoTable
swL2VlanPortInfoTable.description: A table containing the VLAN and port role information of each port.

swL2VlanPortInfoEntry.name: swL2VlanPortInfoEntry
swL2VlanPortInfoEntry.description: The table entry of VLAN port information.

swL2VlanPortInfoVid.name: swL2VlanPortInfoVid
swL2VlanPortInfoVid.description: The VLAN ID assigned to a special port

swL2VlanPortInfoPortRole.name: swL2VlanPortInfoPortRole
swL2VlanPortInfoPortRole.description: The port role of a special port. When the role is 'other', it means this port does not belong to the VLAN.

swL2SubnetVLANTable.name: swL2SubnetVLANTable
swL2SubnetVLANTable.description: A table containing the subnet VLAN information.

swL2SubnetVLANEntry.name: swL2SubnetVLANEntry
swL2SubnetVLANEntry.description: The entry of subnet VLAN information.

swL2SubnetVLANIPAddress.name: swL2SubnetVLANIPAddress
swL2SubnetVLANIPAddress.description: This object indicates the IP address.

swL2SubnetVLANIPMask.name: swL2SubnetVLANIPMask
swL2SubnetVLANIPMask.description: This object indicates the IP mask.

swL2SubnetVLANID.name: swL2SubnetVLANID
swL2SubnetVLANID.description: This object indicates the VLAN ID.

swL2SubnetVLANRowStatus.name: swL2SubnetVLANRowStatus
swL2SubnetVLANRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL2VlanPrecedenceTable.name: swL2VlanPrecedenceTable
swL2VlanPrecedenceTable.description: A table containing the VLAN classification precedence information of each port.

swL2VlanPrecedenceEntry.name: swL2VlanPrecedenceEntry
swL2VlanPrecedenceEntry.description: The entry of VLAN classification precedence information.

swL2VlanPrecedencePortIndex.name: swL2VlanPrecedencePortIndex
swL2VlanPrecedencePortIndex.description: This object indicates the port index.

swL2VlanPrecedenceClassification.name: swL2VlanPrecedenceClassification
swL2VlanPrecedenceClassification.description: This object indicates the VLAN classification precedence.

swL2NniGvrpBpduAddress.name: swL2NniGvrpBpduAddress
swL2NniGvrpBpduAddress.description: Specifies the GVRP's BPDU MAC address of the NNI port with Q-in-Q status.

swL2PortInfoTable.name: swL2PortInfoTable
swL2PortInfoTable.description: A table that contains information about every port.

swL2PortInfoEntry.name: swL2PortInfoEntry
swL2PortInfoEntry.description: A list of information for each port of the device.

swL2PortInfoPortIndex.name: swL2PortInfoPortIndex
swL2PortInfoPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortInfoMediumType.name: swL2PortInfoMediumType
swL2PortInfoMediumType.description: Indicates the medium type of the port number.

swL2PortInfoUnitID.name: swL2PortInfoUnitID
swL2PortInfoUnitID.description: Indicates the ID of the unit in the system.

swL2PortInfoType.name: swL2PortInfoType
swL2PortInfoType.description: This object indicates the connector type of this port.

swL2PortInfoLinkStatus.name: swL2PortInfoLinkStatus
swL2PortInfoLinkStatus.description: This object indicates the port link status.

swL2PortInfoNwayStatus.name: swL2PortInfoNwayStatus
swL2PortInfoNwayStatus.description: This object indicates the port speed and duplex mode.

swL2PortInfoModuleType.name: swL2PortInfoModuleType
swL2PortInfoModuleType.description: This object indicates the module type of this port.

swL2PortInfoErrorDisabled.name: swL2PortInfoErrorDisabled
swL2PortInfoErrorDisabled.description: This object indicates the blocking type of this port.

swL2PortCtrlTable.name: swL2PortCtrlTable
swL2PortCtrlTable.description: A table that contains control information about every port.

swL2PortCtrlEntry.name: swL2PortCtrlEntry
swL2PortCtrlEntry.description: A list of control information for each port on the device.

swL2PortCtrlPortIndex.name: swL2PortCtrlPortIndex
swL2PortCtrlPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortCtrlMediumType.name: swL2PortCtrlMediumType
swL2PortCtrlMediumType.description: Indicates the medium type of the port number.

swL2PortCtrlUnitIndex.name: swL2PortCtrlUnitIndex
swL2PortCtrlUnitIndex.description: Indicates the ID of the unit in the device

swL2PortCtrlAdminState.name: swL2PortCtrlAdminState
swL2PortCtrlAdminState.description: This object decides if the port is enabled or disabled.

swL2PortCtrlNwayState.name: swL2PortCtrlNwayState
swL2PortCtrlNwayState.description: Chose the port speed, duplex mode, and N-Way function mode.

swL2PortCtrlFlowCtrlState.name: swL2PortCtrlFlowCtrlState
swL2PortCtrlFlowCtrlState.description: The flow control mechanism is different between full duplex mode and half duplex mode. For half duplex mode, the jamming signal is asserted. For full duplex mode, the IEEE 802.3x flow control function sends PAUSE frames and receives PAUSE frames.

swL2PortCtrlLearningState.name: swL2PortCtrlLearningState
swL2PortCtrlLearningState.description: This object decides if the port is locked or not.

swL2PortCtrlMACNotifyState.name: swL2PortCtrlMACNotifyState
swL2PortCtrlMACNotifyState.description: This object sets each port's MAC notification state.

swL2PortCtrlMDIXState.name: swL2PortCtrlMDIXState
swL2PortCtrlMDIXState.description: This object configures the MDIX setting of the port.

swL2PortCtrlAutoNegRestart.name: swL2PortCtrlAutoNegRestart
swL2PortCtrlAutoNegRestart.description: If the value of this object is set to restart(1) then this will force auto-negotiation to begin link renegotiation. If auto-negotiation signaling is disabled, a write to this object has no effect. Setting the value of this object to norestart(2) has no effect.

swL2PortCtrlAutoNegCapAdvertisedBits.name: swL2PortCtrlAutoNegCapAdvertisedBits
swL2PortCtrlAutoNegCapAdvertisedBits.description: A value that uniquely identifies the set of capabilities advertised by the local auto-negotiation entity. Capabilities in this object that are not available in swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapabilityBits cannot be enabled. Note that the local auto-negotiation entity may advertise some capabilities beyond the scope of this MIB. This is indicated by returning the bit value bOther in addition to any bit values for standard capabilities that are listed in the IANAifMauAutoNegCapBits TC.

swL2PortCtrlJumboFrame.name: swL2PortCtrlJumboFrame
swL2PortCtrlJumboFrame.description: This object configures the switch's jumbo frame settings.

swL2PortCtrlJumboFrameMaxSize.name: swL2PortCtrlJumboFrameMaxSize
swL2PortCtrlJumboFrameMaxSize.description: This object describes how many bytes the max jumbo frame is.

swL2PortCableDiagnosisTable.name: swL2PortCableDiagnosisTable
swL2PortCableDiagnosisTable.description: A table that contains cable diagnostic information about every port.

swL2PortCableDiagnosisEntry.name: swL2PortCableDiagnosisEntry
swL2PortCableDiagnosisEntry.description: A list with cable diagnostic information for each port of the device.

swL2PortCableDiagnosisPortIndex.name: swL2PortCableDiagnosisPortIndex
swL2PortCableDiagnosisPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortCableDiagnosisPairIndex.name: swL2PortCableDiagnosisPairIndex
swL2PortCableDiagnosisPairIndex.description: Indicates the pair index of each port. Pair 1 means pin 3 and 6 of the connector. Pair 2 means pin 1 and 2 of the connector. Pair 3 means pin 7 and 8 of the connector. Pair 4 means pin 4 and 5 of the connector.

swL2PortCableDiagnosisCableStatus.name: swL2PortCableDiagnosisCableStatus
swL2PortCableDiagnosisCableStatus.description: This object indicates the cable status.

swL2PortCableDiagnosisPairStatus.name: swL2PortCableDiagnosisPairStatus
swL2PortCableDiagnosisPairStatus.description: This object indicates the status of the pair.

swL2PortCableDiagnosisPairLength.name: swL2PortCableDiagnosisPairLength
swL2PortCableDiagnosisPairLength.description: This object indicates the approx. length or length to failure of the pair. The unit value is in meters.

swL2PortCableDiagnosisPairLengthInaccura.name: swL2PortCableDiagnosisPairLengthInaccuracy
swL2PortCableDiagnosisPairLengthInaccura.description: This object indicates the inaccuracy of a pair length. The unit value is in meters.

swL2PortCounterCtrlTable.name: swL2PortCounterCtrlTable
swL2PortCounterCtrlTable.description: A table that is used to clear counter information about every port.

swL2PortCounterCtrlEntry.name: swL2PortCounterCtrlEntry
swL2PortCounterCtrlEntry.description: A list of entries used to clear the counter information for each port of the device.

swL2PortCounterCtrlPortIndex.name: swL2PortCounterCtrlPortIndex
swL2PortCounterCtrlPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortCounterClearCtrl.name: swL2PortCounterClearCtrl
swL2PortCounterClearCtrl.description: This object indicates whether to clear the counters for each port of the device or not.

swL2PortErrTable.name: swL2PortErrTable
swL2PortErrTable.description: A table that contains error information for each port.

swL2PortErrEntry.name: swL2PortErrEntry
swL2PortErrEntry.description: A list of information regarding port errors on the device.

swL2PortErrPortIndex.name: swL2PortErrPortIndex
swL2PortErrPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module).

swL2PortErrPortState.name: swL2PortErrPortState
swL2PortErrPortState.description: This object indicates if the port state is enabled or disabled.

swL2PortErrPortConnStatus.name: swL2PortErrPortConnStatus
swL2PortErrPortConnStatus.description: This object indicates whether the Port Status is err-disabled or not.

swL2PortErrPortReason.name: swL2PortErrPortReason
swL2PortErrPortReason.description: This object describes the reason for the port error.

swL2PortAutoNegInfoTable.name: swL2PortAutoNegInfoTable
swL2PortAutoNegInfoTable.description: A table that contains information about every port's auto negotiation status.

swL2PortAutoNegInfoEntry.name: swL2PortAutoNegInfoEntry
swL2PortAutoNegInfoEntry.description: A list of information for each port auto negotiation of the device.

swL2PortAutoNegInfoPortIndex.name: swL2PortAutoNegInfoPortIndex
swL2PortAutoNegInfoPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortAutoNegInfoAdminStatus.name: swL2PortAutoNegInfoAdminStatus
swL2PortAutoNegInfoAdminStatus.description: If the value of this object is disabled(2) then the interface will act as it would if it had no auto-negotiation signaling. The status is affect by setting swL2PortCtrlNwayState.

swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapabilityBits.name: swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapabilityBits
swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapabilityBits.description: A value that uniquely identifies the set of capabilities of the local auto-negotiation entity. Note that interfaces that support this MIB may have capabilities that extend beyond the scope of this MIB. Note that the local auto-negotiation entity may support some capabilities beyond the scope of this MIB. This is indicated by returning the bit value bOther in addition to any bit values for standard capabilities that are listed in the IANAifMauAutoNegCapBits TC.

swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapAdvertisedBits.name: swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapAdvertisedBits
swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapAdvertisedBits.description: A value that uniquely identifies the set of capabilities advertised by the local auto-negotiation entity. Capabilities in this object that are not available in swL2PortAutoNegCapabilityBits cannot be enabled. Note that the local auto-negotiation entity may advertise some capabilities beyond the scope of this MIB. This is indicated by returning the bit value bOther in addition to any bit values for standard capabilities that are listed in the IANAifMauAutoNegCapBits TC.

swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapReceivedBits.name: swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapReceivedBits
swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapReceivedBits.description: A value that uniquely identifies the set of capabilities received from the remote auto-negotiation entity. Note that interfaces that support this MIB may be attached to remote auto-negotiation entities that have capabilities beyond the scope of this MIB. This is indicated by returning the bit value bOther in addition to any bit values for standard capabilities that are listed in the IANAifMauAutoNegCapBits TC.

swL2PortDropCounterTable.name: swL2PortDropCounterTable
swL2PortDropCounterTable.description: A table that contains received error statistic information for each port.

swL2PortDropCounterEntry.name: swL2PortDropCounterEntry
swL2PortDropCounterEntry.description: A list of information for each port received drop counter.

swL2PortDropCounterPortIndex.name: swL2PortDropCounterPortIndex
swL2PortDropCounterPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortBufferFullDrops.name: swL2PortBufferFullDrops
swL2PortBufferFullDrops.description: The total number of packets discarded while input buffer full.

swL2PortACLDrops.name: swL2PortACLDrops
swL2PortACLDrops.description: The total number of received packets denied by ACLs.

swL2PortMulticastDrops.name: swL2PortMulticastDrops
swL2PortMulticastDrops.description: The total number of received multicast packet that is discarded.

swL2PortVLANIngressDrops.name: swL2PortVLANIngressDrops
swL2PortVLANIngressDrops.description: The total number of packets discarded by VLAN ingress checking.

swL2PortIngressBandwidthControlDrops.name: swL2PortIngressBandwidthControlDrops
swL2PortIngressBandwidthControlDrops.description: The total number of packets discarded by port ingress bandwidth control.

swL2PortInvalidIPv6Drops.name: swL2PortInvalidIPv6Drops
swL2PortInvalidIPv6Drops.description: The total number of packets discarded by IPv6 L3

swL2PortSTPDrops.name: swL2PortSTPDrops
swL2PortSTPDrops.description: The total number of packets discarded when ingress port is not in forwarding state.

swL2PortStormAndFDBDiscard.name: swL2PortStormAndFDBDiscard
swL2PortStormAndFDBDiscard.description: The total number of packets discarded by receiving policy (i.e. DST_DISCARD, SRC_DISCARD,RATE_CONTROL, etc.)

swL2PortMTUDrops.name: swL2PortMTUDrops
swL2PortMTUDrops.description: The total number of packets discarded by frames received, which exceeds Maximum Frame in length and contains a valid or invalid FCS.

swL2PortInvalidDestinationPort.name: swL2PortInvalidDestinationPort
swL2PortInvalidDestinationPort.description: The total number of packets dropped due to port bitmap of zero condition.

swL2PortJumboFrameCtrlTable.name: swL2PortJumboFrameCtrlTable
swL2PortJumboFrameCtrlTable.description: A table that contains information for each port's jumbo frame information.

swL2PortJumboFrameCtrlEntry.name: swL2PortJumboFrameCtrlEntry
swL2PortJumboFrameCtrlEntry.description: A list of information for each port's jumbo frame of the device.

swL2PortJumboFrameCtrlPortIndex.name: swL2PortJumboFrameCtrlPortIndex
swL2PortJumboFrameCtrlPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.

swL2PortJumboFrameCtrlState.name: swL2PortJumboFrameCtrlState
swL2PortJumboFrameCtrlState.description: This object indicates the jumbo frame state on a specified port.

swL2PortSfpInfoTable.name: swL2PortSfpInfoTable
swL2PortSfpInfoTable.description: A table that contains information for each sfp pluged in port.

swL2PortSfpInfoEntry.name: swL2PortSfpInfoEntry
swL2PortSfpInfoEntry.description: A list of information for each sfp pluged in port.

swL2PortSfpInfoPortIndex.name: swL2PortSfpInfoPortIndex
swL2PortSfpInfoPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortSfpInfoVendorName.name: swL2PortSfpInfoVendorName
swL2PortSfpInfoVendorName.description: The vendor name of sfp informaiton.

swL2PortSfpInfoVendorPN.name: swL2PortSfpInfoVendorPN
swL2PortSfpInfoVendorPN.description: The vendor PN of sfp informaiton.

swL2PortSfpInfoVendorSN.name: swL2PortSfpInfoVendorSN
swL2PortSfpInfoVendorSN.description: The vendor SN of sfp informaiton.

swL2PortSfpInfoVendorOUI.name: swL2PortSfpInfoVendorOUI
swL2PortSfpInfoVendorOUI.description: The vendor OUI of sfp information.

swL2PortSfpInfoVendorRev.name: swL2PortSfpInfoVendorRev
swL2PortSfpInfoVendorRev.description: The vendor Rev of sfp information.

swL2PortSfpInfoDateCode.name: swL2PortSfpInfoDateCode
swL2PortSfpInfoDateCode.description: The date code of sfp information.

swL2PortSfpInfoFiberType.name: swL2PortSfpInfoFiberType
swL2PortSfpInfoFiberType.description: The fiber type of sfp information.

swL2PortSfpInfoBaudRate.name: swL2PortSfpInfoBaudRate
swL2PortSfpInfoBaudRate.description: The baud rate of sfp information.

swL2PortLinkTimeTable.name: swL2PortLinkTimeTable
swL2PortLinkTimeTable.description: A table of information for the link time of the port.

swL2PortLinkTimeEntry.name: swL2PortLinkTimeEntry
swL2PortLinkTimeEntry.description: An entry in swL2PortLinkTimeTable contains the link time of the port.

swL2PortLinkTimeIfIndex.name: swL2PortLinkTimeIfIndex
swL2PortLinkTimeIfIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortLinkTimer.name: swL2PortLinkTimer
swL2PortLinkTimer.description: The link timer of the port after the port is link up When the value is 0 means the port is link down.

swL2TrunkMaxSupportedEntries.name: swL2TrunkMaxSupportedEntries
swL2TrunkMaxSupportedEntries.description: Maximum number of entries in the trunk configuration table (swL2TrunkCtrlTable).

swL2TrunkCurrentNumEntries.name: swL2TrunkCurrentNumEntries

swL2TrunkCtrlTable.name: swL2TrunkCtrlTable
swL2TrunkCtrlTable.description: This table specifies information about the logical port trunk groups.

swL2TrunkCtrlEntry.name: swL2TrunkCtrlEntry
swL2TrunkCtrlEntry.description: A list of information about each logical port trunk group.

swL2TrunkIndex.name: swL2TrunkIndex
swL2TrunkIndex.description: The index number of the logical port trunk group. The trunk group number depends on the existence of unit and module.

swL2TrunkName.name: swL2TrunkName
swL2TrunkName.description: The name of the logical port trunk group.

swL2TrunkMasterPort.name: swL2TrunkMasterPort
swL2TrunkMasterPort.description: This object indicates the master port number of the port trunk entry. When using Port Trunking, you cannot configure the other ports of the group except the master port. Their configuration must be the same as the master port (e.g. speed, duplex, enabled/disabled, flow control, and so on).

swL2TrunkMember.name: swL2TrunkMember
swL2TrunkMember.description: Indicates the number of ports included in this Trunk group. The trunk port number depends on the existence of the module. The maximum number of ports is 8 for one trunk group.

swL2TrunkFloodingPort.name: swL2TrunkFloodingPort
swL2TrunkFloodingPort.description: The object indicates the flooding port number of the port trunk entry. The first port of the Trunk group is implicitly configured to be the flooding port.

swL2TrunkType.name: swL2TrunkType
swL2TrunkType.description: This object indicates the type of trunk group. static: is a static trunk group lacp: is a LACP trunk group.

swL2TrunkState.name: swL2TrunkState
swL2TrunkState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL2TrunkAlgorithm.name: swL2TrunkAlgorithm
swL2TrunkAlgorithm.description: This object configures part of the packet examined by the switch when selecting the egress port for transmitting load-sharing data.

swL2TrunkLACPPortTable.name: swL2TrunkLACPPortTable
swL2TrunkLACPPortTable.description: This table specifies which ports are grouped together (this can be up to 8 ports) into a single logical link.

swL2TrunkLACPPortEntry.name: swL2TrunkLACPPortEntry
swL2TrunkLACPPortEntry.description: A list of information specifying which ports are grouped together (this can be up to 8 ports) into a single logical link.

swL2TrunkLACPPortIndex.name: swL2TrunkLACPPortIndex
swL2TrunkLACPPortIndex.description: The index of logical port LACP.

swL2TrunkLACPPortState.name: swL2TrunkLACPPortState
swL2TrunkLACPPortState.description: The state of a logical port LACP.

swL2TrunkVLANTable.name: swL2TrunkVLANTable
swL2TrunkVLANTable.description: This table is used to manage the VLAN trunking feature of the device.

swL2TrunkVLANEntry.name: swL2TrunkVLANEntry
swL2TrunkVLANEntry.description: This object is used to configure the VLAN trunking settings for each port.

swL2TrunkVLANPort.name: swL2TrunkVLANPort
swL2TrunkVLANPort.description: This object indicates the port being configured.

swL2TrunkVLANState.name: swL2TrunkVLANState
swL2TrunkVLANState.description: The state of the logical port LACP.

swL2MirrorLogicTargetPort.name: swL2MirrorLogicTargetPort
swL2MirrorLogicTargetPort.description: This object indicates which switch port will sniff another port. The port number is the sequential (logical) number, which is also applied to the bridge MIB, etc.

swL2MirrorPortSourceIngress.name: swL2MirrorPortSourceIngress
swL2MirrorPortSourceIngress.description: This represents the port where ingress packets will be sniffed.

swL2MirrorPortSourceEgress.name: swL2MirrorPortSourceEgress
swL2MirrorPortSourceEgress.description: This represents the port where egress packets will be sniffed.

swL2MirrorPortState.name: swL2MirrorPortState
swL2MirrorPortState.description: This object indicates the port mirroring state. other (1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. disabled (2) - After writing this value to the object, the corresponding entry will be removed from the table. enabled (3) - This entry resides in the table.

swL2MirrorGroupTable.name: swL2MirrorGroupTable
swL2MirrorGroupTable.description: This table specifies information about the mirror group configuration.

swL2MirrorGroupEntry.description: A list of information about each mirror group configuration.

swL2MirrorGroupRowStatus.name: swL2MirrorGroupRowStatus
swL2MirrorGroupRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL2MirrorGroupState.name: swL2MirrorGroupState
swL2MirrorGroupState.description: This object indicates the mirror group state.

swL2MirrorGroupTargetPort.name: swL2MirrorGroupTargetPort
swL2MirrorGroupTargetPort.description: This object indicates the mirror group target port.

swL2MirrorGroupSourceIngress.description: This object indicates the mirror group ingress source ports.

swL2MirrorGroupSourceEgress.name: swL2MirrorGroupSourceEgress
swL2MirrorGroupSourceEgress.description: This object indicates the mirror group egress source ports.

swL2IGMPAccessAuthTable.name: swL2IGMPAccessAuthTable
swL2IGMPAccessAuthTable.description: This table is used to manage the IGMP Access Authentication configurations of the device.

swL2IGMPAccessAuthEntry.name: swL2IGMPAccessAuthEntry
swL2IGMPAccessAuthEntry.description: A list of manageable entities for IGMP Access Authentication. The configuration is done per port.

swL2IGMPAccessAuthPort.name: swL2IGMPAccessAuthPort
swL2IGMPAccessAuthPort.description: The index of the swL2IGMPAccessAuthTable. This object corresponds to the port being configured.

swL2IGMPAccessAuthState.name: swL2IGMPAccessAuthState
swL2IGMPAccessAuthState.description: This object denotes the status of IGMP Access Authentication of the port. Note: enabled(1): Both the authentication and accounting functions are enabled, after the client is authenticated, the accounting message will be sent to Radius. disabled(2): Both the authentication and accounting functions are disabled. auth_only(3): Only the authentication function is enabled, after the client is authenticated, accounting message will not be sent to Radius. accounting_only(4): Only the accounting function is enabled, authentication is not needed, if the client joins a group, the accounting message will be sent to Radius.

swL2TrafficCtrlTable.name: swL2TrafficCtrlTable

swL2TrafficCtrlGroupIndex.name: swL2TrafficCtrlGroupIndex

swL2TrafficCtrlUnitIndex.name: swL2TrafficCtrlUnitIndex

swL2TrafficCtrlBMStromthreshold.name: swL2TrafficCtrlBMStromthreshold
swL2TrafficCtrlBMStromthreshold.description: This object decides how many thousand broadcast/multicast packets per second (depending on swL2TrafficCtrlBcastStromCtrl, swL2TrafficCtrlMcastStromCtrl or swL2TrafficCtrlDlfStromCtrl objects being enabled) will activate the storm control function. Whenever a port reaches its configured amount of packets in the one second time interval, the device will start dropping that type of packet, until the time interval has expired. Once the time interval has expired, the device will restart forwarding that type of packet.

swL2TrafficCtrlBcastStromCtrl.name: swL2TrafficCtrlBcastStromCtrl
swL2TrafficCtrlBcastStromCtrl.description: This object indicates if the broadcast storm control function is enabled or disabled.

swL2TrafficCtrlMcastStromCtrl.name: swL2TrafficCtrlMcastStromCtrl

swL2TrafficCtrlDlfStromCtrl.name: swL2TrafficCtrlDlfStromCtrl
swL2TrafficCtrlDlfStromCtrl.description: This object indicates if the destination lookup fail function is enabled or disabled.

swL2TrafficSegTable.name: swL2TrafficSegTable

swL2TrafficSegEntry.description: A list of information which specifies the port with its traffic forwarding list.

swL2TrafficSegForwardPorts.name: swL2TrafficSegForwardPorts

swL2LoopDetectTrapMode.name: swL2LoopDetectTrapMode
swL2LoopDetectTrapMode.description: This object indicates the loopback detection trap mode for the system.

swL2LoopDetectPortTable.name: swL2LoopDetectPortTable
swL2LoopDetectPortTable.description: The table specifies the loopback detection function specified by port.

swL2macNotifyInfo.description: This object indicates the information for the device MAC address changes. And the detailed information include: Operation Code + MAC address + Box ID + Port Number + Zero... Operation Code: 1, 2 1 means learned a new MAC address 2 means deleted a old MAC address. Box ID: The switch box ID, for standalone device, it always 1. Port Number: The port number learned or deleted for the box. Zero: Used to separate each message(Operate Code + MAC address + Box ID + Port Number).
